28.10.2 Pointer-To-Integer and Integer-To-Pointer
-------------------------------------------------

Because pointer size does not necessarily equal integer size, use the
follow macros to do it right.

        PTR2UV(pointer)
        PTR2IV(pointer)
        PTR2NV(pointer)
        INT2PTR(pointertotype, integer)

   For example:

        IV  iv = ...;
        SV *sv = INT2PTR(SV*, iv);

   and

        AV *av = ...;
        UV  uv = PTR2UV(av);


