 my ($logmessage, $priority) = @_;       # common
 my $logmessage = $_[0];                 # uncommon, and ugly

   Subroutines can also return values:

 sub square {
     my $num = shift;
     my $result = $num * $num;
     return $result;
 }

   Then use it like:

 $sq = square(8);

   For more information on writing subroutines, see *note perlsub
NAME::.


